        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 22 at 6:30PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 630 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northwest of Cloverdale, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cloverdale, Camp Garza, Animas Peak, Geronimo Pass, and Skeleton
Canyon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
